---
title: Bloom Works 11ty + Decap Prototype
layout: base-layout.njk
sections:
  - type: image
    image: /images/uploads/home-hero.jpg
    width: full
  - type: html
    html: |-
      <div class="home-hero-text full-wrapper">
      <div class="standard-wrapper">
        Better services start with putting
        <span class="change">
          <del>technology</del>
          <ins>people</ins>
        </span>
        &nbsp;first.

        <style>
        .home-hero-text {
          background-color: var(--grey-light);
        }
        .home-hero-text .standard-wrapper {
          font-size: 3rem;
          font-weight: 700;
          line-height: 1.1;
          padding: 2rem 1rem 5rem;
        }

        .home-hero-text .change {
          z-index: 1;
          position: relative;
          display: inline-block;
        }

        .home-hero-text del {
          text-decoration: none;
        }

        .home-hero-text del::before {
          content: " ";
          position: absolute;
          left: 0;
          right: 0;
          bottom: 15px;
          height: 8px;
          background-color: #37a576;
          transform: rotate(-4deg);
          z-index: 100;
        }

        .home-hero-text ins {
          color: #37a576;
          font-family: Permanent Marker,Marker Felt,Comic Sans;
          position: absolute;
          top: 110%;
          left: 50%;
          text-decoration: none;
        }
        .home-hero-text ins::before {
          content: "^";
          margin-right: 1rem;
          position: relative;
        }
        </style>
      </div>
      </div>
  - type: imageAndText
    image: data:image/svg+xml;base64,
    background: "#b6decd"
    text: >-
      We're **building a better future** with our partners.


      Bloom Works is a woman-owned public benefit company that helps organizations serve people better. Digital services are part of everyday life — we use them for everything from accessing information online to figuring out which public services we qualify for. At Bloom, we work with governments and nonprofits to meet those digital service needs — and create products that are beautiful and easy to use.
  - type: text
    text: >-
      # Let’s work together.


      At Bloom, we work closely with our partners to understand their pain points and vision. And we transform that vision into reality with creative, practical, and data-driven solutions.


      We’re a seasoned group of technologists, designers, and storytellers. Many of us have worked in the public sector with groups like USDS, and others hail from the best tech companies the private sector has to offer.  We've also lived the struggles of many of our partners. We've had .gov and .org emails. We've worked with legacy systems and resource-strapped staff. And we know that even when the end goal is clear, the path to get there often isn’t. We've made it our business to navigate those complex paths and build elegant solutions using best-in-class technology.


      **Check out our [case studies](/experiences/).**


      **Want to work with us? [Get in touch](mailto:hello@bloomworks.digital).**


      **Lean about our [capabilities and contracting details](/services/).**
---
{# TODO: this should be more generically implemented in an include #}
{% for section in sections %}
  {% if section.type === "text" %}
    <div class="standard-wrapper">
      {{ section.text | renderContent("md") | safe }}
    </div>
  {% elif section.type === "image" %}
    <div class="image-block {% if section.width == 'full' %}full-wrapper{% else %}standard-wrapper{% endif %}">
      <img
        src="{{ section.image }}"
        alt="{{ section.alt }}"
        style="
          {% if section.width == 'auto' %}
            max-width: 100%;
          {% else %}
            width: 100%;
          {% endif %}
        "
      >
    </div>
  {% elif section.type === "imageAndText" %}
    <div
      class="image-and-text"
      {% if section.background %}style="background-color: {{ section.background }};"{% endif %}
    >
      <div class="standard-wrapper">
        <img class="image-and-text--img" src="{{ section.image }}" alt="{{ section.alt }}">
        <div class="image-and-text--text">
          {{ section.text | renderContent("md") | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  {% elif section.type === "html" %}
    {# TODO: Should parse and make sure no elements left open before declaring safe #}
    {{ section.html | safe }}
  {% else %}
    <div class="standard-wrapper">
      Type: {{ section.type }}
    </div>
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}
